{
  "analysis": "The tokenization is working correctly (token IDs 464 3616 286 1204 318 are the correct GPT-2 tokens for 'The meaning of life is'), but the byte decoding is wrong. I found a bug in the lb function: memcpy(rb[256+x]+rl[ri],...) should be memcpy(rb[256+x]+rl[li],...). The offset for copying the right token's bytes should use the left token's length, not the right token's length. This same bug also affects the 'stereotypical' output in the main program - the model might actually be generating correct tokens but they're all being decoded wrong.",
  "plan": "Fix the rb memcpy bug in both files, recompile, and retest.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/memcpy(rb\\[256+x\\]+rl\\[ri\\],rb\\[ri\\]/memcpy(rb[256+x]+rl[li],rb[ri]/g' /app/gpt2.c /app/test.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep 'memcpy(rb' /app/gpt2.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "gcc -O3 -o /app/test /app/test.c -lm 2>&1 && gcc -O3 -o /app/a.out /app/gpt2.c -lm 2>&1\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ]
}
